\n956: - Register subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n957: - Implement error handler `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n958:   - Print error message in red\n959:   - If verbose: print traceback\n960:   - Raise `typer.Exit(1)`\n961: \n962: #### 46. `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n963: **Purpose**: Pydantic models for metadata validation.\n964: \n965: **Logic**:\n966: - Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model:\n967:   - `agent_name: str`\n968:   - `language: str` (validator: must be `python`, `java`, etc.)\n969:   - `entrypoint: str`\n970:   - `port: int` (validator: 1-65535)\n971:   - `build_mode: str` (validator: `local`, `cloud`)\n972:   - `version: str`\n973:   - `description: str`\n974:   - `router_url: str | None`\n975:   - `workload_manager_url: str | None`\n976:   - `agent_id: str | None`\n977:   - `session_id: str | None`\n978:   - `status: str | None`\n979: \n980: #### 47. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n981: **Purpose**: Load and save agent metadata YAML.\n982: \n983: **Logic**:\n984: - Class `MetadataService`:\n985:   - `load_metadata(workspace_path) -> AgentMetadata`:\n986:     - Try `agent_metadata.yaml`, fall back to `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml`\n987:     - Parse YAML, validate with Pydantic\n988:   - `save_metadata(metadata, workspace_path)`:\n989:     - Write to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n990:     - Use `yaml.dump` with proper formatting\n991:   - `update_metadata(metadata, updates)`: merge changes\n992: \n993: #### 48. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n994: **Purpose**: Docker SDK wrapper for image operations.\n995: \n996: **Logic**:\n997: - Class `DockerService`:\n998:   - `check_docker_available()`: raise `RuntimeError` if Docker unavailable\n999:   - `build_image(workspace_path, image_name, tag, buildargs=None) -> dict`:\n1000:     - Use `docker.from_env()`\n1001:     - Call `docker.images.build()`\n1002:     - Return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n1003:   - `push_image(image_name, registry_url=None, username=None, password=None) -> dict`:\n1004:     - Login if credentials provided\n1005:     - Retag if needed\n1006:     - Stream push logs\n1007:     - Return `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n1008:   - `remove_image(image_name) -> bool`: remove and handle errors\n1009: \n1010: #### 49. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n1011: **Purpose**: Standard Kubernetes deployment provider.\n1012: \n1013: **Logic**:\n1014: - Class `KubernetesProvider`:\n1015:   - `__init__()`: initialize Kubernetes client\n1016:   - `deploy_agent(config) -> dict`:\n1017:     - Create/patch Deployment\n1018:     - Create/patch NodePort Service\n1019:     - Return deployment info\n1020:   - `wait_for_deployment_ready(deployment_name, namespace, timeout=120)`:\n1021:     - Poll deployment status\n1022:     - Raise `TimeoutError` on timeout\n1023:   - `delete_agent(deployment_name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1024:     - Delete Deployment and Service\n1025:     - Ignore 404 errors\n1026:   - `get_agent_status(deployment_name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1027:     - Return pod status\n1028: \n1029: #### 50. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n1030: **Purpose**: AgentCube CRD provider.\n1031: \n1032: **Logic**:\n1033: - Class `AgentCubeProvider`:\n1034:   - `__init__()`: initialize Kubernetes client with custom API\n1035:   - `deploy_agent_runtime(config) -> dict`:\n1036:     - Build AgentRuntime CR object\n1037:     - Create/patch via CustomObjects API\n1038:     - Set env vars: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`\n1039:     - Set `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n1040:   - `get_agent_runtime_status(name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1041:     - Get CR from API\n1042:     - Extract status from `.status`\n1043:   - `delete_agent_runtime(name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1044:     - Delete CR, ignore 404\n1045: \n1046: #### 51. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n1047: **Purpose**: Pack command implementation.\n1048: \n1049: **Logic**:\n1050: - Class `PackRuntime`:\n1051:   - `__init__(metadata_overrides)`: store overrides\n1052:   - `pack(workspace_path) -> tuple[str, str]`:\n1053:     - Validate workspace exists and is directory\n1054:     - Validate language-specific requirements (Python: *.py files, Java: pom.xml)\n1055:     - Load or create metadata\n1056:     - Merge CLI overrides\n1057:     - Optionally generate Dockerfile\n1058:     - Save metadata\n1059:     - Return `(agent_name, metadata_path)`\n1060: \n1061: #### 52. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n1062: **Purpose**: Build command implementation.\n1063: \n1064: **Logic**:\n1065: - Class `BuildRuntime`:\n1066:   - `__init__(proxy=None, cloud_provider=None)`: store config\n1067:   - `build(workspace_path) -> dict`:\n1068:     - Load metadata\n1069:     - Increment version (patch bump)\n1070:     - Check Docker availability for local build\n1071:     - Call `DockerService.build_image()`\n1072:     - Update metadata with image info\n1073:     - On failure: revert version\n1074:     - Return build result\n1075: \n1076: ---\n1077: \n1078: ## AR-032: CLI Toolkit — Publish, Invoke, Status Commands\n1079: \n1080: ### Files to Create\n1081: \n1082: #### 53. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n1083: **Purpose**: Publish command implementation.\n1084: \n1085: **Logic**:\n1086: - Class `PublishRuntime`:\n1087:   - `__init__(provider, version=None, image_url=None, ...)`: store config\n1088:   - `publish(workspace_path) -> dict`:\n1089:     - Load metadata\n1090:     - If provider `agentcube`:\n1091:       - Validate `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` present\n1092:       - Use `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n1093:     - If provider `k8s`:\n1094:       - Use `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()`\n1095:       - Wait for deployment ready\n1096:     - Update metadata with deployment info\n1097:     - Return publish result\n1098: \n1099: #### 54. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n1100: **Purpose**: Invoke command implementation.\n1101: \n1102: **Logic**:\n1103: - Class `InvokeRuntime`:\n1104:   - `__init__(provider, headers=None)`: store config\n1105:   - `invoke(workspace_path, payload) -> dict`:\n1106:     - Load metadata\n1107:     - Build target URL:\n1108:       - If AgentRuntime CR: `{base}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/`\n1109:       - Else: from metadata\n1110:     - Add headers:\n1111:       - `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` if session_id in metadata\n1112:       - Custom headers from CLI\n1113:     - POST JSON payload\n1114:     - Return response\n1115: \n1116: #### 55. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n1117: **Purpose**: Status command implementation.\n1118: \n1119: **Logic**:\n1120: - Class `StatusRuntime`:\n1121:   - `__init__(provider)`: store config\n1122:   - `get_status(workspace_path) -> dict`:\n1123:     - Load metadata\n1124:     - If no `agent_id`: return `status=not_published`\n1125:     - If provider `agentcube`:\n1126:       - Call `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime_status()`\n1127:     - If provider `k8s`:\n1128:       - Call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n1129:     - Return status dict\n1130: \n1131: #### 56. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/pack.py`\n1132: **Purpose**: Pack subcommand definition.\n1133: \n1134: **Logic**:\n1135: - Define `@app.command(\"pack\")`:\n1136:   - Options: `workspace`, `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`, `description`, `output`, `verbose`\n1137:   - Use `Progress` spinner\n1138:   - Call `PackRuntime.pack()`\n1139:   - Print success or handle error\n1140: \n1141: #### 57. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/build.py`\n1142: **Purpose**: Build subcommand definition.\n1143: \n1144: **Logic**:\n1145: - Define `@app.command(\"build\")`:\n1146:   - Options: `workspace`, `proxy`, `cloud_provider`, `output`, `verbose`\n1147:   - Call `BuildRuntime.build()`\n1148:   - Print build result\n1149:   - Handle errors\n1150: \n1151: #### 58. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/publish.py`\n1152: **Purpose**: Publish subcommand definition.\n1153: \n1154: **Logic**:\n1155: - Define `@app.command(\"publish\")`:\n1156:   - Options: `workspace`, `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`, `verbose`\n1157:   - Call `PublishRuntime.publish()`\n1158:   - Print deployment info\n1159: \n1160: #### 59. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/invoke.py`\n1161: **Purpose**: Invoke subcommand definition.\n1162: \n1163: **Logic**:\n1164: - Define `@app.command(\"invoke\")`:\n1165:   - Options: `workspace`, `payload`, `header` (repeatable), `provider`, `verbose`\n1166:   - Parse payload as JSON (exit 1 if invalid)\n1167:   - Parse headers as `key:value` (exit 1 if invalid format)\n1168:   - Call `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`\n1169:   - Print response\n1170: \n1171: #### 60. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/status.py`\n1172: **Purpose**: Status subcommand definition.\n1173: \n1174: **Logic**:\n1175: - Define `@app.command(\"status\")`:\n1176:   - Options: `workspace`, `provider`, `verbose`\n1177:   - Call `StatusRuntime.get_status()`\n1178:   - Display Rich Table with status info\n1179:   - Exit 1 if `not_published` or `error`\n1180: \n1181: ---\n1182: \n1183: ## AR-033: Python SDK — Clients and Exceptions\n1184: \n1185: ### Files to Create\n1186: \n1187: #### 61. `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n1188: **Purpose**: Python SDK project metadata.\n1189: \n1190: **Content**:\n1191: ```toml\n1192: [build-system]\n1193: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n1194: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n1195: \n1196: [project]\n1197: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n1198: version = \"0.0.10\"\n1199: description = \"Python SDK for AgentCube sandbox orchestration\"\n1200: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n1201: dependencies = [\n1202:     \"requests>=2.31.0\",\n1203: ]\n1204: \n1205: [project.optional-dependencies]\n1206: dev = [\n1207:     \"pytest>=7.0.0\",\n1208:     \"pytest-cov>=4.0.0\",\n1209: ]\n1210: ```\n1211: \n1212: #### 62. `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n1213: **Purpose**: Package initialization with public API exports.\n1214: \n1215: **Content**:\n1216: ```python\n1217: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n1218: from agentcube.agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n1219: \n1220: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n1221: ```\n1222: \n1223: #### 63. `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n1224: **Purpose**: Exception hierarchy for SDK errors.\n1225: \n1226: **Logic**:\n1227: - Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)`: base exception\n1228: - Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)`:\n1229:   - Constructor: `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n1230:   - Store as instance attributes\n1231: - Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)`: session-related errors\n1232: - Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)`: data plane errors\n1233: \n1234: #### 64. `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n1235: **Purpose**: Workload Manager HTTP client.\n1236: \n1237: **Logic**:\n1238: - Class `ControlPlaneClient`:\n1239:   - `__init__(workload_manager_url, auth_token=None)`:\n1240:     - Resolve URL from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env\n1241:     - Resolve token from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n1242:     - Create `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n1243:     - Set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` if present\n1244:   - `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600) -> str`:\n1245:     - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n1246:     - JSON: `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}`\n1247:     - Return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError`\n1248:   - `delete_session(session_id) -> bool`:\n1249:     - DELETE to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n1250:     - Return True on 404 or success, False on other errors\n1251: \n1252: #### 65. `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n1253: **Purpose**: Router data plane client for Code Interpreter.\n1254: \n1255: **Logic**:\n1256: - Class `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`:\n1257:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, cr_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1258:     - Build base URL using `urljoin`\n1259:     - Create `requests.Session`\n1260:     - Set default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n1261:   - `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n1262:     - Add timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n1263:     - Raise on HTTP errors\n1264:   - `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1265:     - POST to `api/execute`\n1266:     - JSON: `{command: [...], timeout: \"<n>s\"}`\n1267:     - If `exit_code != 0`: raise `CommandExecutionError`\n1268:   - `write_file(path, content, mode=\"0644\")`:\n1269:     - POST to `api/files` with base64 content\n1270:   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`:\n1271:     - Multipart POST to `api/files`\n1272:   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`:\n1273:     - GET from `api/files/{path}`, stream to file\n1274:   - `list_files(path) -> list`:\n1275:     - GET from `api/files?path={path}`\n1276: \n1277: #### 66. `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n1278: **Purpose**: Router data plane client for Agent Runtime.\n1279: \n1280: **Logic**:\n1281: - Class `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`:\n1282:   - `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n1283:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1284:     - Build invocation base URL\n1285:     - Create `requests.Session`\n1286:   - `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n1287:     - Add timeout tuple\n1288:   - `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1289:     - POST JSON to invocation URL\n1290:     - Set `SESSION_HEADER` and `Content-Type`\n1291: \n1292: #### 67. `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n1293: **Purpose**: High-level Code Interpreter client.\n1294: \n1295: **Logic**:\n1296: - Class `CodeInterpreterClient`:\n1297:   - `__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url=None, name=None, namespace=\"default\", session_id=None, ttl=3600, timeout=120)`:\n1298:     - Validate `router_url` is provided (arg or `ROUTER_URL` env)\n1299:     - Store config\n1300:     - If `session_id` not provided:\n1301:       - Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n1302:       - Call `create_session()`\n1303:       - Handle failure: delete session, re-raise\n1304:     - Call `_init_data_plane()`\n1305:   - `_init_data_plane()`:\n1306:     - Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with session_id\n1307:   - `__enter__()`: return self\n1308:   - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `stop()`\n1309:   - `stop()`:\n1310:     - Close data plane session\n1311:     - If created session: call `delete_session()`\n1312:     - Close control plane session\n1313:   - `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`: delegate to data plane\n1314:   - `run_code(code, language=\"python\") -> dict`:\n1315:     - Write timestamped `.py` file\n1316:     - Execute `python3 <file>`\n1317:   - `write_file(path, content)`: delegate\n1318:   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`: delegate\n1319:   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`: delegate\n1320:   - `list_files(path) -> list`: delegate\n1321: \n1322: #### 68. `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n1323: **Purpose**: High-level Agent Runtime client.\n1324: \n1325: **Logic**:\n1326: - Class `AgentRuntimeClient`:\n1327:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1328:     - Store config\n1329:     - If `session_id` not provided:\n1330:       - GET from invocation base URL\n1331:       - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` from response header\n1332:       - Raise `ValueError` if missing\n1333:     - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n1334:   - `__enter__()`: return self\n1335:   - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `close()`\n1336:   - `close()`: close underlying session\n1337:   - `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1338:     - If no session_id: raise `ValueError`\n1339:     - Delegate to data plane\n1340: \n1341: #### 69. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n1342: **Purpose**: HTTP utility functions.\n1343: \n1344: **Logic**:\n1345: - `read_token_from_file(path) -> str | None`:\n1346:   - Read file, return stripped contents\n1347:   - Handle FileNotFoundError, return None\n1348: - `create_session(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0) -> tuple`:\n1349:   - Create `requests.Session`\n1350:   - Mount `HTTPAdapter` with pool settings\n1351:   - Return session and timeout tuple\n1352: \n1353: #### 70. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n1354: **Purpose**: General utility functions.\n1355: \n1356: **Logic**:\n1357: - `ensure_dir(path)`: create directory if not exists\n1358: - `generate_timestamp() -> str`: ISO format timestamp\n1359: - `base64_encode(data) -> str`: standard base64 encoding\n1360: - `base64_decode(s) -> bytes`: standard base64 decoding\n1361: \n1362: #### 71. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n1363: **Purpose**: Logging configuration.\n1364: \n1365: **Logic**:\n1366: - `setup_logging(level=logging.INFO)`:\n1367:   - Configure root logger with format\n1368:   - Return logger instance\n1369: \n1370: ---\n1371: \n1372: ## File Summary\n1373: \n1374: | File Count | Category |\n1375: |------------|----------|\n1376: | 10 | AR-023: Dify Plugin Manifest |\n1377: | 8 | AR-024: Dify Tool Schema |\n1378: | 5 | AR-025: PCAP Analyzer |\n1379: | 6 | AR-026: Helm Workload Manager |\n1380: | 5 | AR-027: Helm Router |\n1381: | 8 | AR-028: Helm CRDs & Volcano |\n1382: | 4 | AR-029: Dockerfiles & Makefile |\n1383: | 3 | AR-030: GitHub Actions |\n1384: | 10 | AR-031: CLI Pack/Build |\n1385: | 8 | AR-032: CLI Publish/Invoke/Status |\n1386: | 11 | AR-033: Python SDK |\n1387: | **Total: 78 files** |\n1388: \n1389: ---\n1390: \n1391: ## Implementation Phases\n1392: \n1393: ### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2)\n1394: 1. **Python SDK (AR-033)**: Create core SDK clients and exceptions\n1395: 2. **Helm Chart Base (AR-026, AR-027, AR-028)**: Set up chart structure, CRDs, and base templates\n1396: 3. **Dockerfiles (AR-029)**: Create multi-stage builds for all Go binaries\n1397: \n1398: ### Phase 2: Integrations (Week 2-3)\n1399: 1. **Dify Plugin (AR-023, AR-024)**: Implement plugin manifest, provider, and tool schemas\n1400: 2. **CLI Toolkit (AR-031, AR-032)**: Build CLI commands for pack, build, publish, invoke, status\n1401: \n1402: ### Phase 3: Examples and CI/CD (Week 3-4)\n1403: 1. **PCAP Analyzer (AR-025)**: Create example FastAPI service\n1404: 2. **CI/CD Pipelines (AR-030)**: Set up GitHub Actions workflows\n1405: \n1406: ### Phase 4: Testing and Polish (Week 4-5)\n1407: 1. **Integration Tests**: End-to-end tests for all components\n1408: 2. **Documentation**: README files and guides\n1409: 3. **Performance Optimization**: Optimize bottlenecks\n1410: \n1411: ---\n1412: \n1413: ## Dependencies and Prerequisites\n1414: \n1415: ### External Dependencies\n1416: - Go 1.24+ for control plane components\n1417: - Python 3.10+ for SDK, CLI, and integrations\n1418: - Kubernetes 1.28+ cluster with CRD support\n1419: - Helm 3.x for chart installation\n1420: - Docker with Buildx for multi-arch images\n1421: - Redis 6+ for session storage\n1422: \n1423: ### Internal Dependencies\n1424: - SDK must be built before CLI and Dify plugin\n1425: - CRDs must exist before deploying Workload Manager/Router\n1426: - Helm chart must be complete before CI/CD pipelines\n1427: \n1428: ---\n1429: \n1430: ## Risk Mitigation\n1431: \n1432: ### High Priority Risks\n1433: 1. **Dify Plugin Compatibility**: Test against latest Dify version early\n1434: 2. **Kubernetes RBAC**: Verify ClusterRole permissions match actual usage\n1435: 3. **Session Management**: Ensure proper cleanup in SDK context managers\n1436: \n1437: ### Mitigation Strategies\n1438: - Implement comprehensive error handling in all clients\n1439: - Use connection pooling and timeouts for HTTP clients\n1440: - Add health checks and monitoring endpoints\n1441: - Create rollback procedures for deployments\n\n(End of file - total 1441 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Implementation Plan — AR-023 through AR-033\n\nThis plan maps Architectural Requirements AR-023 through AR-033 to specific files and implementation details based on the specifications in `./specs/`.\n\n## AR Mapping Overview\n\n| AR | Spec Domain | Package/Path | Description |\n|----|-------------|--------------|-------------|\n| AR-023 | integrations | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | Dify plugin manifest and provider structure |\n| AR-024 | integrations | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | Dify tool schema and implementation |\n| AR-025 | example | `example/pcap-analyzer/` | PCAP analyzer FastAPI service |\n| AR-026 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart templates for Workload Manager |\n| AR-027 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart templates for Router |\n| AR-028 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart RBAC and optional Volcano scheduler |\n| AR-029 | deployment | `docker/`, `Makefile` | Dockerfiles and build targets |\n| AR-030 | ci-cd | `.github/workflows/` | GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines |\n| AR-031 | cli-toolkit | `cmd/cli/agentcube/` | CLI pack/build commands |\n| AR-032 | cli-toolkit | `cmd/cli/agentcube/` | CLI publish/invoke/status commands |\n| AR-033 | python-sdk | `sdk-python/agentcube/` | SDK clients and exception hierarchy |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"PLAN.md","time":{"start":1775881057813,"end":1775881057833}}}}
